1
00:00:10,891 --> 00:00:12,991
Hyun Jae.

2
00:00:19,064 --> 00:00:20,698
Hyun Jae.

3
00:00:20,698 --> 00:00:22,591
Kim Hyun Jae!

4
00:00:24,264 --> 00:00:26,545
Where did he go?

5
00:00:35,210 --> 00:00:40,517
<i>Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

6
00:00:49,749 --> 00:00:52,456
- Brother!
- Khun.

7
00:00:52,456 --> 00:00:54,276
How have you been?

8
00:00:54,276 --> 00:00:56,423
Seems like Korea was fun.

9
00:00:57,256 --> 00:00:59,042
Who's this?

10
00:01:04,709 --> 00:01:06,568
Friend...

11
00:01:07,636 --> 00:01:10,983
My boyfriend. Shin Jae Min.

12
00:01:14,689 --> 00:01:15,713
Jae Min.

13
00:01:15,713 --> 00:01:16,729
Yes?

14
00:01:16,729 --> 00:01:18,543
He's my cousin.

15
00:01:18,543 --> 00:01:20,276
Nice to meet you.

16
00:01:21,363 --> 00:01:22,669
I'm Shin Jae Min.

17
00:01:22,669 --> 00:01:25,189
- Must have been troublesome to get here.
- No, not at all.

18
00:01:25,189 --> 00:01:27,040
By the way, your Korean is amazing.

19
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:30,320
I spent a few years in Korea because of work.

20
00:01:31,056 --> 00:01:32,243
Khun.

21
00:01:32,243 --> 00:01:33,400
You like Korea, don't you?

22
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,780
Yeah. It's damn great.

23
00:01:36,996 --> 00:01:39,096
- Let's go.
- Let's go eat.

24
00:01:48,496 --> 00:01:49,796
No, stay seated.

25
00:01:49,796 --> 00:01:51,663
Thank you.

26
00:01:51,663 --> 00:01:55,129
This is actually a secret lodge,
only open to family members.

27
00:01:55,129 --> 00:01:58,196
I've never seen Khun bring anyone else here.

28
00:01:58,196 --> 00:01:59,994
Thank you.

29
00:02:00,769 --> 00:02:04,229
For helping Khun come back here.

30
00:02:09,476 --> 00:02:11,478
Enjoy your meal, Khun.

31
00:02:12,903 --> 00:02:14,383
Aren't you eating with us?

32
00:02:14,383 --> 00:02:16,929
I only stopped by to check on Khun.

33
00:02:16,929 --> 00:02:18,902
See you again.

34
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:21,596
I'm leaving.

35
00:02:21,596 --> 00:02:23,328
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

36
00:02:30,276 --> 00:02:31,969
Why aren't you eating?

37
00:02:31,969 --> 00:02:33,543
Why don't you eat?

38
00:02:33,543 --> 00:02:35,396
Well, I don't know where to start.

39
00:02:35,396 --> 00:02:37,496
They all look so good.

40
00:02:45,189 --> 00:02:47,549
Whoa! What is this?

41
00:02:47,549 --> 00:02:49,083
It tastes so good!

42
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:52,316
How is it so good? What is it? Huh?

43
00:02:53,529 --> 00:02:55,035
Cute.

44
00:02:55,636 --> 00:02:57,736
Hm? What?

45
00:02:59,016 --> 00:03:01,603
I said, you eat well.

46
00:03:02,243 --> 00:03:05,263
Hey, you should try it, too.
It's out of this world.

47
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:11,249
From this day on,

48
00:04:11,249 --> 00:04:14,650
you are going back to being trainees.

49
00:04:16,403 --> 00:04:18,436
We have decided that you
can't make a debut by yourselves.

50
00:04:18,436 --> 00:04:21,256
The boy band project has been scrapped.

51
00:04:22,229 --> 00:04:24,449
Is this because of Jae Min?

52
00:04:24,449 --> 00:04:26,629
Not necessarily.

53
00:04:26,629 --> 00:04:29,908
The board decided to
focus on Hyun Jae's solo debut.

54
00:04:29,908 --> 00:04:33,936
So don't get any ideas
and concentrate on your training.

55
00:04:33,936 --> 00:04:35,481
Let's go.

56
00:04:38,576 --> 00:04:40,569
Is this about Jae Min?

57
00:04:40,569 --> 00:04:43,249
We could just do without Shin Jae Min.

58
00:04:43,249 --> 00:04:44,943
What's with all this drama?

59
00:04:44,943 --> 00:04:47,423
- How does this make any sense?
- It doesn't.

60
00:04:47,423 --> 00:04:49,609
There's no way.

61
00:04:49,609 --> 00:04:51,668
We already had a debut song.

62
00:04:51,668 --> 00:04:55,068
This is some hidden camera prank, right?

63
00:05:07,903 --> 00:05:09,750
What happened?

64
00:05:12,996 --> 00:05:15,023
What do you think?

65
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:17,456
Didn't you hear?

66
00:05:17,456 --> 00:05:20,265
You knew about this, didn't you?

67
00:05:24,676 --> 00:05:26,700
You knew, and you still did all that?

68
00:05:28,069 --> 00:05:30,369
It's the company's decision.

69
00:05:30,369 --> 00:05:33,656
- What was I supposed to do?
- You knew!

70
00:05:35,063 --> 00:05:37,082
You knew, and yet...

71
00:05:37,803 --> 00:05:39,903
You took me out to eat.

72
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:44,285
- You even took me to bed.
- This isn't new for us.

73
00:05:45,896 --> 00:05:47,996
It's not the first time this has happened.

74
00:05:53,629 --> 00:05:56,516
Ah, Hyun Jae. There you are.

75
00:05:56,516 --> 00:05:58,996
- I was looking for you.
- Sir.

76
00:05:58,996 --> 00:06:00,769
What is it?

77
00:06:00,769 --> 00:06:03,223
The American producer that
I told you about last time...

78
00:06:03,223 --> 00:06:05,356
We got the contract.

79
00:06:05,356 --> 00:06:08,229
There's a Zoom meeting in an hour.
Meet me in my room.

80
00:06:08,229 --> 00:06:10,636
Yes, thank you, sir.

81
00:06:11,843 --> 00:06:14,490
I have great expectations for you.

82
00:06:15,496 --> 00:06:17,576
I'll do my best.

83
00:06:17,576 --> 00:06:19,609
That's the spirit.

84
00:06:19,609 --> 00:06:20,753
You do your best, too.

85
00:06:20,753 --> 00:06:23,045
You'll get a chance someday.

86
00:07:39,289 --> 00:07:42,059
I've never been to a house
with a private pool before.

87
00:07:43,363 --> 00:07:45,789
You're a good swimmer.

88
00:07:45,789 --> 00:07:48,112
I like being in water.

89
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,070
That's one more thing...

90
00:07:53,743 --> 00:07:55,843
I know about you now.

91
00:08:34,316 --> 00:08:36,416
Slow down.

92
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:45,307
Trying to pass out again?

93
00:08:50,016 --> 00:08:52,027
It's not like that.

94
00:09:02,623 --> 00:09:04,867
I have a question.

95
00:09:07,683 --> 00:09:09,318
What is it?

96
00:09:11,423 --> 00:09:13,798
Your reply to my letter.

97
00:09:30,996 --> 00:09:32,519
My reply.

98
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:42,646
It's too late.

99
00:09:42,646 --> 00:09:44,846
We should sleep.

100
00:09:44,846 --> 00:09:46,693
Which room do you want?

101
00:09:46,693 --> 00:09:48,472
Just pick one.

102
00:09:56,153 --> 00:09:58,253
I want to stay with you.

103
00:10:17,246 --> 00:10:19,346
<i>Make me some ramen, will you?</i>

104
00:10:28,859 --> 00:10:31,033
I never should have brought him here.

105
00:10:34,433 --> 00:10:36,886
How am I supposed to live here now?

106
00:10:45,002 --> 00:10:47,282
This is mockery, nothing less.

107
00:11:09,389 --> 00:11:11,401
Hyun Jae, we need to talk.

108
00:11:11,989 --> 00:11:14,082
Still have something to say?

109
00:11:14,082 --> 00:11:16,556
I'm fine with not getting to debut.

110
00:11:16,556 --> 00:11:20,269
I can congratulate you on your
solo career with my whole heart, so...

111
00:11:21,482 --> 00:11:24,176
- Hyun Jae, please, just...
- Yoon Soo An.

112
00:11:25,862 --> 00:11:28,031
This isn't like you.

113
00:11:32,022 --> 00:11:35,282
I'll take anything, just not this.

114
00:11:35,282 --> 00:11:37,796
You never used to be like this.

115
00:11:37,796 --> 00:11:39,996
This isn't the real you!

116
00:11:39,996 --> 00:11:42,494
What's really wrong with you?

117
00:11:48,682 --> 00:11:51,338
Since when were you so clingy?

118
00:11:52,709 --> 00:11:54,809
Just stop already.

119
00:12:14,149 --> 00:12:16,029
Thank you.

120
00:12:18,882 --> 00:12:21,825
I could finally breathe, thanks to you.

121
00:12:26,242 --> 00:12:28,809
If I had stayed in Korea...

122
00:12:32,499 --> 00:12:35,777
I've been thinking, watching you here.

123
00:12:36,552 --> 00:12:39,652
You must've needed a place to breathe as well.

124
00:12:40,945 --> 00:12:43,412
That's why you came to Korea, right?

125
00:12:49,465 --> 00:12:52,880
It must be hard for you being here.

126
00:12:54,132 --> 00:12:56,779
You did this for me, didn't you?

127
00:12:57,712 --> 00:12:59,652
If it's too hard for you...

128
00:12:59,652 --> 00:13:02,898
we can go back to Korea first thing tomorrow.

129
00:13:04,192 --> 00:13:06,519
You know...

130
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:10,397
I can breathe anywhere with you by my side.

131
00:15:57,425 --> 00:15:59,685
- Has anyone got a hold of Hyun Jae yet?
- No, he's not picking up.

132
00:15:59,685 --> 00:16:02,445
Well, he has to be somewhere, right?

133
00:16:02,445 --> 00:16:05,012
Where on earth did he go?
We're supposed to be recording today!

134
00:16:05,012 --> 00:16:07,192
Come on, pick up.

135
00:16:09,085 --> 00:16:10,761
He's not home, either.

136
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:12,985
We just couldn't find him anywhere.

137
00:16:12,985 --> 00:16:14,369
He's gone without a trace.

138
00:16:14,369 --> 00:16:17,075
Darn it. Come with me!

139
00:16:24,712 --> 00:16:30,025
<i>No one is available to take your call.
Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

140
00:16:44,859 --> 00:16:46,485
Who's calling?

141
00:16:46,485 --> 00:16:48,792
I just thought of somewhere I want to go.

142
00:16:48,792 --> 00:16:51,328
I teamed you two up for better performance...

143
00:16:51,328 --> 00:16:52,772
but apparently, you've been dating.

144
00:16:52,772 --> 00:16:54,784
Excuse me.

145
00:16:56,419 --> 00:16:58,052
Who are you?

146
00:16:58,052 --> 00:16:59,952
Were you spying on me this whole time?

147
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:01,239
Kim Hyun Jae.

148
00:17:01,239 --> 00:17:03,665
Want to see something funny?

149
00:17:05,212 --> 00:17:07,968
You thought you made it
because you're talented, didn't you?

